Description.Text: The overall impression of this hotel is that it is a clean, well-maintained property for its class, ideal for all types of leisure travelers.

The hotel is situated in the heart of Bayswater on a quiet side street just off the Bayswater Road opposite Hyde Park, less than 5 minutes walk from Queensway and Bayswater underground stations (Central, Circle, and District Lines).
On average the rooms are small in size, and in good condition, decorated in pale, neutral colors. The bathrooms are also in good condition.
A converted townhouse dating back to the early 1900s.
There is no restaurant as such but a large breakfast room is located adjacent to the reception.
The lobby is small but welcoming, decorated in creams with a beige marble floor.
